Gerry McQuade

Bio

PhD candidate in economics at Lancaster University Management School. My research interests are in early childhood development and skill formation, the socio-economic impacts of climate and environmental shocks, and the interaction between these two processes in low and middle income contexts.

I will be a visiting student at ODID, University of Oxford, during trinity term 2023.

Long suffering Scottish rugby fan.
